k\geq 0
k\in\mathbb{N} 
n\in\mathbb{R} 
\int_{(2n-1)\pi}^{(2n+1)\pi}\left|x-2n\pi\right|\cos(k x)\mathrm dx
a_k
 2\,{\frac {2\, \left( -1 \right) ^{k} \left( \cos \left( \pi \,kn  \right)  \right) ^{2}-2\, \left( \cos \left( \pi \,kn \right)   \right) ^{2}+ \left( -1 \right) ^{k+1}+1}{{k}^{2}}} . 
 2\,{\frac {\cos \left( 2\,\pi \,kn \right)  \left(  \left( -1 \right)  ^{k}-1 \right) }{{k}^{2}}}.
x-2n\pi=t
|t|\cos(kt)
|t|\sin(kt)
\int_{(2n-1)\pi}^{(2n+1)\pi}\left|x-2n\pi\right|\cos(k x)\mathrm dx=\int_{-\pi}^{\pi}|t| \cos(kt+2kn\pi)\,dt
\cos(2kn\pi)\int_{-\pi}^{\pi}|t|\cos(kt)\,dt-\sin(2kn\pi)\int_{-\pi}^{\pi}|t|\sin(kt)\,dt
\int_{-\pi}^{\pi}|t| \cos(kt+2kn\pi)\,dt=2\cos(2kn\pi)\int_{0}^{\pi}t\cos(kt)\,dt=\frac{2 \left((-1)^k-1\right) (\cos  (2 \pi  k n))}{k^2}
